"BT MAGIC: Wizardry ","Ahem.

Another idea- brace yourselves against immediate reaction! 

There are 8 ""macro-Wizardries"",that is to say Wizardries which have
Wizardries underneath them:

Abjuration, Alteration, Conjuration, Divination, Enchantment,
Elemental,  Evocation, and Summoning 

Now... what if those were really not ""W:""s = at least not ones that
humans had access to?  

What if all Wizardries were created equal and there were only the basic
patterns and not the one one level up.  In other words..
There would no longer be a skill called W: Abjuration, there would only
be W: Shaping, W: Binding, W:Warding. 

This is how the Elemental ones have been running for a while- I think it
would be a good thing if all of them ran like that.  

""But Alex,"" you say, ""I am have RANK 10 in Abjuration and only RANK 4 in
the sub-schools!""

I say, ""DOn't worry!""(at which point you wince!:-)) I would have you get
the Initial SKill Level Value of the macro-pattern and distribute it
amongst the lesser patterns!  This is a good thing for you!  Your SCF is
likely to go up! 

""But Alex,"" you say, ""I bacame a specialist because of the 6% per rank
for the sub-schools!""  

I say ""Don't worry! I am going to let you increase your skill to osme
fair number such that you don't get screwed!""

""But ALex,"" you say, ""I am an elf and have a RANK 14 in ABJURATION!""

""DOn't worry!"" I say, ""Elves have invented an Abjuration- we will talk
and you will, I think, be happiest of all of my Faeries!""

What do you think?  But there's mORE!!!!  Tell them what they have WON! 

ADVANTAGES:

All wizardries handled the same
No special rules!  
More variety and spice to Wizards! 

NOW: PART 2! The special RULES!  :-):-):-)

The macro-patterns existence - though not ""w:""s or skills- do give one
BIG advantage: they allow for advancment in the sister ""w:""s before you
reach RANK 8 in any one.  In other words you would be able to have RANK
5 in Binding, RANK 3 in Shaping , and RANK 2 in WARDING because they are
related.


I like this flavor alot!  Comments? 


