made some assumptions about the cause of the breakdown of the machine which
I now believe were either 100% wrong or partially incomplete.  There
appears to have been a significant Divine influence in the breakdown of the
machine with the direct intention being to then arrange for the isolation
of the Heartstone.  I never considered that the same entities that took out
the machine would be the ones that would back the isolation.  And that they
wanted that to occur so that they could initiate a major reality change.
Something really big just happened while we were in Valhalla, and I have no
idea just how widespread the effects are.

Another mistake on my part was that although I knew:
That the effect of the isolation would be to allow non-isolated Context
Symbols to expand with significantly less resistance; 
That it would be much more difficult for reality shifts that affected the
Prime to occur;
That a new Symbol representing the Prime would, over time, be regenerated; 

I did not realize that the time scale for that regeneration was non-linear
and that it would be drastically accelerated by any Context wide reality
shifts which occurred.  Ie, As soon as Rismaeon has the machine repaired he
has access to power, though it won't be at the same level as before unless
either time passes, additional reality shifts occur, or we bring back the
other symbol.
