"BT: Prefix shorthand for Skills ","In all the conversations that have been going on, I've found myself picking
up on something that has rubbed me the wrong way for a while.  The prefixes
that we currently use to categorize skills on the character sheets aren't
always clear and I'd like to make a proposal to correct that.

These are the current prefixes that we use to categorize skills on the
character sheets.  In cases where we have changed the term that we use to
refer to something, I've written new-term (old-term):

G:      General Skills

R:      Rune systems
L:       Spoken Language (casting language or conversational language)
R/W:  Read/Write language (casting language or conversational language)

Lore:  Any lore skill

          Thaumaturgies  -  No official one that I know of.
          Alchemical Processes           
                                 -  No official one that I know of.  

          Natural Magics  -  No official one that I know of.  
          Craft Magics     -  No official one that I know of.

S:      Sorceries
M:      Wizardries 
             - Workings(Spells), Rituals, Rites and Incantations(Invokations)
W:     Wizardry Patterns(Schools)           
             - The skill represents your attunement to a Wizardry Pattern
          Disciplines        -  No official one that I know of.

         Divine skills       (under DVF)  -  No official one that I know of.
D:      Divine Links      (under DVF)
            - The skill represents the intensity of your relationship 
              with a Will Pattern.
G:      Divine Gifts       (under DVF)
P:      Priestly Rituals (under INF.  Basic ceremonies: weddings, 
              barmitzvahs, funerals, last rites, mass, etc)

I:        Incarnate Magics
          Creation Magics  -  No official one that I know of.


This is what I would suggest using:

G:      General Skills
          For Example: 
          G: Thunder Plateau school of Electromancy.
            - General skill representing your knowledge of, 
              and attunement to, a specific Wizardry School

R:      Rune systems
L:       Spoken Language (casting language or conversational language)
R/W:  Read/Write language (casting language or conversational language)

Lore:  Any lore skill

T:       Thaumaturgies
A:       Alchemical Processes

          Natural Magics   -- Alex?
          Craft Magics       -- Alex?

S:      Sorceries
W:     Wizardries  - Workings, Rituals, Rites and Incantations
        -> If one skill at different levels, then: W1:, W2:, W3:, W4:
WP:   Wizardry Patterns  
        -> The skill represents attunement to a Wizardry Pattern

DI:      Discipline One spells
DII:     Discipline Two spells
DIII:    Discipline Three spells
                               
D:      Divine prayers           (under DVF)
         (These are not spells or skills, but rather 
           requests/prayers/supplications/invocations)
         Prime examples being Summon Divine Aid, Bless, 
            Absorb Faith, and Heal.
DP:    Divine Patterns         (under DVF)
            - The skill representing the intensity of your relationship 
              with a Will Pattern. 
          Examples: DP:Heimdel, DP:Corellan, DP:Earth
DG:    Divine Gifts               (under DVF)
P:       Priestly Ceremonies (under INF).  
            - Basic ceremonies: weddings, barmitzvahs, funerals, 
              last rites, mass, etc)

I:        Incarnate Magics
          Creation Magics

