"RE: Run dates and otherwise","Well, I talked to Alex and got answers for the in-game calendar
stuff.

All months are 28 days long.  In addition, there are two
inter-calendral festival weeks, not counted on the 'official'
record, at the summer and winter solstice.  These are six or seven
days, the exact number chosen by local wizards or astrologers.
I'm assuming (for ease of calculation) that the summer week is
always seven days and they mess with the winter week, letting us
not worry about the leap year when counting days.

Using this, May 1st = 5/1 = (5-1)*28 +1 = 113

The year as such would be 12*28 +13 = 350 days long (max), making
it about 5% shorter than ours.  Thus a BT 20-year-old would look
19 to us, and a 40-year-old would look 28.  I can live with that.
(Also, Alex, if you want to mess with the length of the days,
making them, say, around 5% longer, you can do that, too.)

The other interesting date (well, to me) would be Eman's birthday,
on Day 299.

299 = 10*28 +19 = (11-1) +7(summer week) +12 = November 12th.
(Hey!  He's a Scorpio!)

...And I like the seasonality, too.

