"Re: Bardic Tales Revision 6.0","Be careful what you wish for.  Here are my thoughts...

On level factors modifying XP rolls:
Be careful taking advice from a character with a level factor over 100.
There is a chance his view of the world might be a tad skewed. :-)
Personally I do not think factor/10 is too much, and as a sworn math
athiest I greatly prefer a simple decimal place shift over even the most
basic division.  If that does not convince you, think of it as a persons
ability to teach themself in a field they understand, then compare it to
the mod for someone else teaching them (rank 1 Teacher = 30 Lvl factor).

On guns:
Just for the record I think the changes to the gun system are basically
good (even though Stephen got severly slammed by them in combo with
enforcement of previously uninforced mods).  I am very happy to see
damage per rank added back in for guns--I really like to see game
mechanics applied as broadly as possible.

I would like to propose two changes though.  First, I think all guns
should have a zero difficulty modifier.  I agree with getting rid of the
bonus to hit, and with the pattern you have set up (that short barrels
are less accurate than long).  However, you have already modeled this
with ranges.  Short barrel guns have shorter ranges, and will take mods
for range sooner than long barrel guns.  This also has the advantage of
getting rid of one more set of modifiers to remember.  (I am also a big
fan of simplification.)

I do not remember the mods to damage for range, but I thought they were
pretty severe.  Do bullets lose that much velocity by long and extra
long range?  (I do not know.)  From a playability standpoint, if I hit
somebody at extra long range (which Stephen now has a base -7% chance to
do now), I would be really disappointed if it only did a couple points
of damage.  On such a low percentage shot, I would feel robbed as a
player if the bullet didn't actually hurt a little when it hit! :-)

