Yea- what he said.  Except:

10 Speed points cuts a skill in half.  Thereafter, every ten speed
points will drop the WSD linearly by one count until one is reached.  
Then 20 points cuts it in half.

It used to be that you could buy off the Draw, and the Targeting at 2
 SPD per count.  I am going to change that in REV 6 unless otherwise 
enrolled.

There will be three seperate actions: Draw, Target, and FIre.  Draw
speed is based on the length of weapon and the ""holster"".  Firing will 
always be two counts- base trigger-pull speed.  Targeting changes from
weapon to weapon, but so long as the weapon is pointed in the 
right hex it will be 4 counts.

If your target stays in the same hex(60 degree angle centered on 
your line of fire) and range (the weapon's range categories) you do 
not have to re-target.  You can keep pulling the trigger.  Any change 
in target, range, or hex causes the shooter to need to re-target.

Right now I am saying they are three seperate actions that need to be
sped up exactly as any skill.  To ease game play though i would allow
you to roll Quickstrike once at the beginning of a pre-set draw, target,
and fire sequence and have that quickstike apply to all three actions.
So: (react) + DRAW_SPEED + (react) + TARGET + (react) + PULL_TRIGGER
TARGET= 4 counts, PULL_TRIGGER= 2 counts
Then: (react) + PULL_TRIGGER + (react) + PULL_TRIGGER... etc. 
	(if on same opponent, in same hex, at same range)

BTW: Drawing, targeting and firing is slow:  one second(five counts) is
considered a laser fast draw-shoot time.  And that is with competition
holsters and cutdown guns, with hand over the gun....


