base speed of any action as the time it takes an average person to do an 
action with an average quality result, whether it is building a house or 
throwing a punch.  [lots of atheistic math not quoted]
     
<Myth>

I think I have to agree with Jeff, here.  It makes more sense to me for an 
8-count action to be as difficult to reduce to 2 counts as a 32-count 
action is to reduce to 8 counts.

Aside from additional penalties due to physics (less-than-1-count actions, 
for instance), a simple geometric system should cover it.  Perhaps charging 
10 speed points to reduce to 1/2, and an additional 10 for each half of the 
remainder.  Charge an additional 10 points to go to a 1-count action, and 
you're there.

(Okay, you can poke holes in my math now.)

