The way BT is run, speed can be used on ANY action.  In theory, every
level factor could be argued to contribute to speed.  A jazz guitarist,
for example, needs to react quickly to play those spiffy riffs and keep
up with the ever changing improvisation.  In actual play though, when is
speed really important?  When your life is in danger.  In a combat
situation.  That is when speed is really important, and I believe people
who are in lots of combat situations react more quickly because their
lives depend upon developing that ability.  That is why PCF and AGF
should contribute to speed.  High speed chases justify VHF.  And I think
that missile and magical combat is just as deadly, and those who engage
in it should be faster.  If anything, I would drop DXF since speed is
not a critical part of most DXF skills.
