> > an action can be is XXX."")
> 
> Ummm... no it still has the same problem.  1 count is still one count.
> Beyond that I have to start fudging.  Just like now.
> 
My point was that with a linear scale for spending SPD, high level
characters will constantly push the barrier and make you work with
smaller and smaller fractions of a count.  With a geometricallly
increasing scale, characters still have some chance of breaking a new
barrier of speed, but they will effectively ""top out"" at quarter speed,
and only the extremely good or lucky will hit eighth speed.
