"Re[2]: BTR6A - QUICK E-MAN"," Well, E-Man finally made it to work (Sorry, Lisa), and I have the first 
 numbers.
 
 
 STM 9.8 -> 16.5  
 
 Very nice, but not too surprising given the larger LVF numbers and the 
 smaller divisor.  I expect to see fallout from this all over my 
 spreadsheet this weekend.  (Though I'll be careful not to gloat about my 
 new SCF near Mordenith.)
 
 
 SPD 7 -> 12 -> 10 -> 7.5
 
 Well, it was a fun ride, anyhow.  Actually, I'll be making out quite well 
 with SCF skills.  The save here is mostly due to E-man's high Discernment.
 
 
 MAB 15 -> 15
 
 The higher level factors cancel out the harsher (to E-Man, anyway) 
 formula.
 
 
 DEF 28 -> 15
 
 Sad, but not critically so.  E-Man has never really been a combat 
 character, and should be able to survive the loss.  (Besides, it's a fair 
 trade for that higher SCF.)
 
 
 Sample Action:
 
 Ladiees and Gentlemen!  For your amusement and edification, Erithmaeon the 
 Weaver will now cast an Air Shield!  <wild applause>
 
 This is normally a 10-count sorcery at 118%.  
 Not using his focus gets E-Man a penalty of -10%.
 
 
 Basic Speed - 7.5
 SCF Mods -    5.45  (Hm.  Better raise that SCF.)
 Skill Mods -  2     (Rank 4 in Air Shield)
 G: Mods -     1.5   (Rank 5 in S:Air)
 Secondary -   2.5   (Rank 7 in W:Air)
 Secondary -   1.0   (Rank 4 in Summon Air)
              -----
 Total Speed   19.95  
 
 We divide this into action (10) and reaction (9).
 
 
 Roll 2d6 for initiative.  This is reaction time.  Get the typical '7'.  
 Buying this down to zero leaves me with 2 reaction speed points.  I put 
 them into instant set-up, gaining a few extra percent in the skill. (+6%)
 
 The action takes 10 counts.  For 10 action speed points, I can buy this 
 down to 5 counts.  The next level of reduction (3 counts) is 16 points, or 
 8 points per count.  
 
 A) At -10% per speed point, I stop here.  Further reduction is not worth a 
 -80%.
 
 B) At -5% per speed count I look into further reduction.  -40% is livable, 
 at my skill levels, particularly if I invoke my focus.
 
 
 A) 118% + 6% - 10% = 114% in five counts.
 
 B) 118% + 6% + 10% (decide to use focus) - 40% = 94% in four counts.
 
 
 Option A seems fine.  E-Man can pretty consistantly do half-speed 
 castings, but is unlikely to reduce things much further.  I am comfortable 
 with that at his level.
 
 Option B makes him a little faster, a little more daring, and a little 
 more inclined to play up the mods.
 
 
 
 All comments are welcome, especially ones complaining that E-Man is too 
 gross and warps the system just by being there.
 
 
                                   -Myth.
 


