No, it is not at all unreasonable for a PCF 60 person to be much more
effective than an unskilled person.  I like the skill bonuses.  I just
think they are too high in proportion to the weapon based damage.  I
think Chuck should be dangerous with a mushy banana, I just think he
should be much much more dangerous with a club or staff.  When you add
20 points of damage from strenght and skill, the weapon doesn't count
for much.  I think if too martial artists squared off, one highly
skilled in punch and the other highly skilled in a weapon, the martial
artist with the weapon should still have a significant advantage.

We have several martial artists of moderate skill in the group, but even
though I am completely unskilled in club, I would trade one punch for
one club swing with any of them.  I might not be so bold with Stephen
Segal or George Forman, so there is some point at which skill bonuses
definately do outstrip the weapon damage.  My point is that I think this
level is much higher than in the current BT system.

As it stands, weapons lose their advantage as people get more skilled in
them.  Ideally point of skill would increase the rolled damage by 5% or
something like that instead of a flat point adder.  I don't like the
idea of a cap in BT either.  In my system the weapon damages are much
higher relative to body points, so a cap works a bit better.  Even at
that, I think I will change my system to allow adding one point of
damage per LoS up to the max damage of the weapon, then one point per 2
LoS beyond that.  That will let people still potentially add infinate
numbers of points, but will give an advantage to large weapons even at
high levels of skill.  I don't know if some version of this would work
in BT or not.

A person with an 18 STR and rank 10 in primary, secondary, tertiary and
G: skills would have a +32 to damage.  This is about the realistic max
for a BT character, since it is pretty difficult to go above 10.  I
would like to see the choice between a punch and a club still have an
noticeable effect even at this level.
