Just in case I wasn't clear... Chuck is a high level martial artist.  I
have no problem with the fact that he could knock somebody out with a
single punch.  I have no with the fact that he could trash somebody with
low skill who was using a weapon.  BUT, I think that if Chuck, or any
very high level martial artist, squared off against an Escrimador of
equal skill, the Escrimador should have a _significant_ advantage.  Of
course, that advantage can be countered with good tactics, etc., but I
think the weapon itself should be an advantage at any level of skill
over having no weapon.

Below is the table Jim created to add in the effect of weapon length on
weapon speed.
> > 
> >                Avg Dam  Spd  ct/40HTK
> > Fist              4       9      90
> > Foot              6      10      66
> > Knee              8      10      50
> > Club              7       8      45
> > 2 Hand Club       9      13      58
> > Quarterstaff     11      10      36
