Geoff, as one of the above mentioned brown belts (who has no skill in
club), I have many thoughts on your question.  I'll try to capture them
all.

1) If my goal was to break the arm, and not just do general damage to
the opponent, then I would be more likely to succeed with karate than
with the club.  My precision is greater, so I good accept the ""real life
called-shot modifiers"" and still have a chance of success.

2) If my opponent was not armed and had no skill in combat (some hapless
low level villager waiting to be bludgeoned) and if my goal was to do
general damage to the opponent, then I think I would do more damage
faster with the club than with my fist or foot.  Note:  I not sure this
is true of inanimate objects.  I suspect I good kick a door open easier
(faster) than I could beat it open with a club.

3) If my opponent was armed or has skill in combat (so now I need to
worry about defending myself) and if my goal was to do general damage to
the opponent, then I would probably damage my opponent and preserve my
own health more effectively with a combination of karate and club.  I
would use  karate's precision until the opponent was stunned or
disarmed, then pummel him/her with the club.

4) To get to what I think you are really asking:  If I was striking my
opponent and they threw up their arm to fend off the blow (random strike
to any arm location), I would be more likely to break the arm if I were
attacking with a club than with my fist or foot.  

Just my opinion.  I hope this helps.
