Here are a few things that I noticed when upgrading Sigmund to use the formulas on the web page.  They may or may not be issues, it is hard for me to tell:

1.	In the description of the MVM secondary stat the formula reads:

MVM = (AGL*2 + STR - BLD -30)/10 + ...

This is different than everywhere else where a character with all 10's gets a stat contribution of zero instead of -1.  Should the subtracted number be a 20 or is Joe normal supposed to have move of 3.5 (5'10"",155#)?

2.	Saves have changed a lot:

It seems odd that the strength save would be based on PCF as a factor.  I know the save skill is a PCF skill and that seems fine but I like the old system in which the save was baed on STM instead of PCF.  It seems out of character for all styles of fighters (including an expert fencer) to have a high save.  I suppose it was worse before in that a sage would get a contribution for his scholarly knowledge but since the STM was never as large as a characters primary factor this did not seem as unbalancing.

On the other side of the scale, since Sigmund is a high level generalist, the new save formulas caused half of his saves to drop dramatically.  For any save in which he previously used STM because it was higher than his factor he now uses PLF or MLF.  Since he is a generalist each of these are about one half of his TLF and so half his saves dropped from around a 100 to around a 60 (he has a 40 TLF so splitting it in half loses a contribution of 20*2 = 40).  This may be intentional but it was a rather dramatic change.

3.	I did not understand the damage column on the weapons table.  I think I missed a discussion somewhere.

