"BT: Endurance","Okay Endurance rears its ugly head once more.  Currently END, EXT, and MEXT
(Endurance, Exhaustion, and Meta-Exhaustion) use the idea that Endurance is
like a pool of energy that you have a certain amount of and that increases
as one becomes more skilled.  Actions use up Endurance like fuel.


ENDURANCE:  Basic ""fuel unit"".  Returns after use at 1 per ten counts....
usually all back in 3-5 minutes.  Resting can double return rate.
EXHAUSTION: EXT comes off the top of END at a rate of 1 per 10 END expended.
It returns at 1 per two hours of rest, 2 per hour of light sleep. 4 per hour
of medium sleep, and 8 per hour of full deep sleep.  Meals can also restore
1-3 EXT three times a day.  meditation is as light sleep.
META-EXHAUSTION: MEXT comes off END as well.  One accumulates one MEXT for
every 10 EXt one accumulates.  It returns at a rate of: 1 per 4 hours of
complete rest, 1 per 2 hours of deep sleep(Deep sleep is usually achieved in
the third hour of sleep)

Now- I have recently been convinced that the recovery system- which is based
on straight point recovery- is not a good analogy to what ""really happens.""
Unfortunately it is  easy and playable.    It has been suggested that we go
to a percentage based system- either you gain X% of your endurance per time
period or run it like HTK... the first quarter come back in minutes, the
next in hours, the next in days.  What do you all think?

