from his Marathon run in three days.  Seems a little long but what the heck.

Sigmund, being a fortu, gets about (8*8) 64 PEX back for an abnormally long
eight hours of shutdown (normally he shuts down for 4 hours a night).  I am
assuming the same eight hour limit applies.  Sigmund recovers from his
marathon run in 6.6 days.

Sounds like apples and oranges at the moment.  Well look at it this way, which
is a much more common usage.  Both Joe and Sigmund were running the
Boston Marathon (27.5 miles) and both of them were doing it by dashing as
fast as they could for short distances and then jogging until they catch there
breath and then dashing again.  Stupid but it serves to make the point.  We
will ignore the PEX cost of jogging since it is small compared to that of dashing.

Joe dashes for 6.8 miles of the race and jogs the remaining 20.7 miles at a
rate of 10.8mph for a total time of 130 minutes or 2:10.  A decent time even
