          ON ENDURANCE

In this conversation Physical and Mental Endurances are equivalent.
Therefore we refer to
END and EXT- but these refer to both Physical Endurance(END) and Mental
Endurance(MEN).
Likewise for exhaustion.  Physical and Mental endurance and exhaustion are
recovered
simultaneously and identically.

Currently END, EXT, and M-EXT (Endurance, Exhaustion, and Meta-Exhaustion)
use the idea that
Endurance is like a pool of energy that you have a certain amount of and
that increases as
one becomes more skilled.  Actions use up Endurance like fuel.

ENDURANCE:  Basic ""fuel unit"".
It returns after use at 1 per ten counts... usually all back in 3-5 minutes.
Resting or
sleeping doubles the return rate.

EXHAUSTION: EXT comes off the top of END at a rate of 1 per 10 END expended.
It returns at 1 per two hours of rest, 2 per hour of light sleep, 4 per hour
of medium
sleep, and 8 per hour of full deep sleep.  Meals can also restore 1-3 EXT
three times a
day.  Meditation is as medium sleep.

META-EXHAUSTION: M-EXT comes off END as well.  One accumulates one M-EXT for
every 10 EXT
one accumulates.

It returns at a rate of: 1 per 4 hours of complete rest, 1 per 2 hours of
deep sleep(Deep
sleep is usually achieved in the third hour of sleep)

Your first hour of sleep is light sleep and gives you 2 EXT, .25 M-EXT
Your second hour of sleep is medium sleep and gives you 4 EXT, .25 M-EXT
All following hours of sleep are deep sleep and give you 8 EXT, 0.5 MEXT

If a character is moving or acting at some percentage of full effort
(travelling with slower
companions, taking their time) they only expend that percentage of the END
cost of the
action.  I.e. if a character has a walk of 1.4 and the group is moving at
.7, she only
expends 50% of the END cost for that type of movement.

Levels of critical can be used to decrease endurance cost just like they can
be used to
increase damage.  The following table describes the effect:

     Levels Of Critical Endurance
- x1
0 x2/3
1 x1/2
2 x2/5
3 x1/3
4 x2/7
5 x1/4
...

Now- I have recently been convinced that the recovery system- which is based
on straight point recovery- is not a good analogy to what ""really happens.""
Unfortunately it is  easy and playable.    It has been suggested that we go
to a percentage based system

PROPOSAL: whenever the rules call for recovering 1 ENDURANCE or EXHAUSTION
it read as 1% of
the character's END or EXT.

PROPOSAL: Character's be allowed to roll against their skills to reduce
endurance loss if
they wish.

