          ON SPEED

Speed Points(SPD PTS) => the number generated by the characters PSPD/MSPD
stat, plus the LVF/10, plus the RANK modifiers: primary(RANK-2),
secondaries([RANK-2]/2), and general([RANK-2]/2).

Initiative points(INIT) => the number subtracted from the characters
initiative roll.  Usually half the speed points, rounded up.

Action Points(ACT) => the points used to speed up actions, perform passive
actions or set-up.  Usually half the speed points, rounded down.
Negative initiative would turn into action points on a 1/1 basis.

Quickstrike would generate SPD PTS- 1 per RANK.    Kata would generate INIT
PTS.  A specific Quickdraw skill would generate 1 ACT per RANK.

To buy 1 ACT => 10% to-hit or 2 points of damage or 1 negative initiative

PROPOSAL: Take damage out of the formula entirely.

One negative initiative point or ACT will buy you:  1 SPD point or 2%-to-hit
or 1 count off
of a passive action (perception, support skill initiation, general skill
activation, etc.)
So 8 ACTION points will buy you a full passive perception or general skill
activation.

--- --- ---
          ON SETUP
Set-up in real counts will give you 5% per count and is limited to:

(1) 10 + KIF/2 counts of set-up AND

(2) a maximum value equal to  (RANK*10+LVF)- or the default value(saves,
MAP, etc.)- of the skill being set-up for.

Do not include secondaries or generals in set-up base chance and do not
include the difficulty of the skill.  Only include the RAW SUCCESS CHANCE:
RANK*10 + LVF.

This is because the more difficult actions are where set-up is really needed
and IMO
makes the most difference in real-life.

The set-up skill allows you to double the set-up bonus per count for the
first RANK counts
of set-up.

--- --- ---
          ON SUPPORT SKILLS


You may no longer roll against support skills.  They give their
3% per rank or 1 SPD point per rank and that is it.  This change alleviates
two problems:
(1) People have been getting high bonuses because they are criticalling
their
support skill rolls.  This is often because of level factor and other
bonuses that already give to the primary skill, so it is redundant bonuses.

(2) This change reduces the number of rolls people have to make in play.
Your
quickstrike just adds Rank in SPD points to your action.  Period!  Your
florentine gives you 3% per rank- period.  No need to do another roll- no
need to recalculate for levels of success, etc.

This is a blessing for people with low ranks because it means you don't fail
your roll either- you always get 6% for your rank 2 support skill!:-)

Support skills can go above the negative modifier for a skill. (I.e. a RANK
15 Florentine
character gets +45% and the minus is only minus 40%.  This person is 5%
better florentining
than not florentining.)

You may use as many support skills as applicable skills you are using.  If
you have unused
support skills they may be used as secondaries.
PROPOSAL:  Support skills can be used as secondary ski
skills when not being used as support
skills

ON KATA/TRANCE/KI FOCUS

>Now does this change effect Ki Focus,

Ki Focus is a separate skill that has no speed effects.  It takes
10 counts to do, and is good for one action.  It allows the user to pour KI
into damage and to-hit chance.  The to-hit bonus for this will also be
limited to the raw SC=> (RANK*10+LVF) or the max damage of the attack.  Adds
RANK/4 to-hit
or RANK/8 in damage per MEN used.

>Mage Trance, Battle Trance,

These also cannot be criticalled- They will make perceptions and all
applicable skills
easier (15% + 3% per rank) and possibly reduce endurance cost while in the
trance state.
When a trance is induced a specific perception is activated.  You must roll
to enter a
trance.  It takes 30 counts, and no crit effects can be used for to-hit
modification.  The
pluses here are also limited to the raw success chance of the primary skill
being modified.

>and Katas ?

As of Rev 6.0 - Kata add 3% per rank to the to-hit chance and they add 1
INIT point per rank
to all actions in the Kata.  It is as a support skill.  All actions in a
Kata sequence are Instant Attacks.

