[Warning Humble Opinion Ahead]

Is a crit roll modified END cost simpler ? I really don't think there is a substantial
difference. I certainly think being able to say I have rank 10 so I use 1/2 the normal
END for this period of time is simpler than saying I have a 160% Success Chance so
my average crit level will be X which will lower my END costs to Y over a period of time.

But currently BT allows both types of modification for Success Chance (SC), Speed, and Damage
Rank modifies all of these statically (SC = +RANK*10, SPD = +RANK-2, and DAM = +RANK-2.
and criticals modify all of these dynamically (see the rapidly fluctuating rules for mods :-) ).
I propose that we extend both mechanisms to END cost.

END cost range is much less elastic than either SPD or DAM so I would suggest some sort of
really limited set of static mods. Maybe something like: END = Cost / ( RANK/4)  with a minimum END cost of
1. This would mean that Rank 12 would only cost 1/3 the normal cost for END.


