==================================
Current Rev 6.0 model for Kata (from website)
==================================

Each different kata is a separate skill. The Kata skill gives 3%/RANKto-hit bonus to the skills within it and w would give [RANK] to the INIT all actions within the kata.

A kata can contain (DRIVE + KATA_RANK)/3 movements at no penalties. Any movement over that adds -10% to the difficulty of the kata. Kata are difficult to learn AND they
become more and more difficult based on how many moves they contain.

Kata act as a secondary to a specific set of sub-skills when those skills are used in a particular fashion and order. The sub-skills are pre-set strings, and are instant attacks (automatic 0
INIT roll, -40 to hit). It takes 4 counts to activate a kata (that can be sped up). The idea being, you have to upload the kata sequence into your forebrain.



