Jim's number's are effectively true for someone whose speed is high enough
to not have a positive initiative.  Low level character's do get a benefit
out of instant attack in that they roll a 0 initiative automatically.

I talked to Jim last night and there were some unclarities  he had:

When you start a sequence of attacks, the first attack is obviously not an
instant attack- you just reacted before it.  The next action is your first
Instant Attack(I.e. attack with no initiative roll).  So the mods are
+0, -40, -60, -80.  SO you don't get the -80 until your fourth attack.

I have also looked at Instant Attack and part of the problem is that people
may be right in that it is too harsh.  It may be more appropriate to do
something like -30, -45, -60; or -40, -50, -60.
PROPOSAL 1: Instant attacks are attacks in which the initiative roll is
automatically adjusted to 0.  It is declared at a reaction, a normal attack
is launched and then the next attack begins the sequence with an INIT roll
of 0 .  The penalties are -40 for the first instant attack, -50 for the next
one, and -60 for all following instant attacks.
As with pre-sets the actions must be declared at the reaction.  Each action
must be specifically declared.  One can declare up to (RANK + DRIVE/3)
actions.  Recurring loops are possible.  For instance: I block high and then
I hit him again and again and again and don't stop till he is dead......

The other point that Jim made that I could actually buy was that it wasn't
broke when we had one INIT per RANK.  Why change it.  So let us look at this
option:

PROPOSAL 2:

Have Kata be a support skill(I.e. above and beyond the secondaries and
generals) to all skills in its umbrella.  It will add 3% per RANK to-hit,
and  RANK in INIT to all of its skills.  All the Skills would be Instant
Attacks, they would be organized into sequences of 2-5 actions with
reactions in between.  One could enter or leave a sequence at the reactions
in-between and those reactions re-set the Instant Attacks. The Kata would
have to be activated  with a successful roll, though no crit would be
possible as in all support skills.   Every sequence written into a Kata
beyond the first would add -10% to the activation roll of the Kata.
Breaking the Kata at a non-reaction carries a +8 penalty. (double the
penalty for missing a normal action.)

Thoughts on both proposals please...?   When I get enough answers I will
post a second summary posts with the changes and stuff.

