"BT: ACT points , ENDURANCE and Contests of Skills.","ON ACT POINTS FROM SUCCESS LEVELS:

Upon further crunching of numbers I realize that I am trying to re-invent
the wheel here.  Given the fundamental logistical problems with retro-active
application of ACT, and the fact that the mechanism already exists to buy
ACT with to-hit (10% to-hit = 1 ACT) I am not sure it is worth us spending
time on it as a concept.

SO.... I would vote for SLs only giving INIT points to the next
reaction.....
...
     Effect of Success Levels on INIT points
SL INIT
1  +2
2  +4
3  +6
4  +8
5  +10
6  +12

NOTE:  INIT points from SL(SL*1.5, round down) go towards the reaction
IMMEDIATELY
after the action (I.e. the character is so much smoother with the action
they can
transition into the next action better.
...

ON GAMBLING FOR ACT POINTS

Peter said:
>I think I understand this concept, and it seems to make sense.  For
>the most part lower level characters wouldn't bother with this, but
