I am a;little confused here Peter- are we talking about ENDURANCE or ACT?
With ACT gambling I think we should forget the idea.    With ENDURANCE I
think it would be a decent system- you know the 5% reduction per rank thing-
but it would mean I would have to balance the END and MEN equations to be a
lot lower (and mind you - as a plus- much more realistic.   Now for many
characters this would not be a big deal.... endurance isn't;t calculated so
often that it would slow the game down EXCEPT for mages.  Mages would have
to calculate their endurance rates for each spell and each time they cast
since amount of spell power- read mental endurance- is not fixed and varies
from application to application.    I am tempted to do something like this
rule but I am concerned about making mages and cyber-warriors spend more
time calculating things.... but then again- they are the ones least likely
to mind sitting on the side calculating while other people do stuff!  :-)

I don't know.  What do people think?

Her is how ENDURANCE  would work:

Warimu the Warrior says ""I cast a Firelance spell"".  Warimu has RANK 5 in
Firelance.  Therefore she is at 75% END cost.  The GM says okay- how many
spell points?  Warimu says: ""I want to do 30 points of DAM, and the base
cost is 10, and it is 1 DAM per 2 spell points so I will put 70 spell points
into it.""  Then, since in the character's environment 1 spell point costs 1
mental endurance(MEN) we need to calculate the cost.  70*.75=52.5=53.  So it
would cost Warimu 53 MEN to cast a 30-point firelance.

Roger the Runner says I am going to run for an hour.  Roger is RANK 7 in
running.  This means he is at 65% END cost for running.  His MVM is 10
(significantly faster than someone with no mvm skill BTW).  His  run speed
is therefore 6 feet/count, or 30 ft/second, or 1800 ft/minute.   (NOTE: This
is really really fast!) The cost for a run is: 1 END/30 counts, or 1
PEX/minute.   Roger has 120 END say.   The run will cost him .65
PEX(Physical Exhaustion) per minute.  So instead of being able to run two
hours Roger will be able to run about 184 minutes or a little over three
hours.

Calculations aren't too bad - I think it might actually work.  Though note-
PEOPLE's END and MEN will go down significantly!  I would leave the base as
it is but all the LVF additions and skill additions will be cut in half.
Thoughts?



