"BT: Examples of contest of skills","Here are some examples.  Note example three shows how Active Defense would
be run differently....

Example 1:  Jane the Jackknife is sneaking up on Gary the Guard.  Jane has a
Move Silently success chance of 100%.  Gary has an Awareness of 120% so his
Awareness success chance to hear Jane sneaking up on him is 120%.
Jane rolls a 43 on her Move Silently.  This is Success Level 2(under half).
Gary rolls a 68 on his awareness.   This is Success Level 1.   Therefore
Gary has 1 Failure level in his perception and does not hear Jane.

Example 2: Alden the Active is swinging his Bastard Sword at Chuck the
Cheeky.
Chuck(assuming appropriate initiative and perception) decides to parry with
his open hand.  Alden's swing chance is 210%.  Chuck's parry chance(with
parry and non-weapon mods) is 160%.  Alden rolls a 98, giving him SL 2.
Chuck rolls a 12, giving him SL 4.  Alden's adjusted SL is now negative two:
(2-4=-2).  Thus he has two levels of failure on his sword swing, and
probably has to roll to hold on to his sword.

Example 3: Alden the Active gets really mad and decides to Great Blow Chuck
the Cheeky's head off.  He swings.  Chuck opts to do an active defense.  He
rolls his active defense.  Alden gets an amazing 4 SLs on his swing.  Chuck
gets 3 SLs on his Defense skill.  Thus Alden's adjusted SL for his Great
Blow is 1.  So Chuck gets hit by a SL 1 sword blow from Alden.

