          ON CONTEST OF SKILLS

I think from now on all contests of skills between characters will be done
with Success Levels instead of ""How much you made it"".

Example 1:  Jane the Jackknife is sneaking up on Gary the Guard.  Jane has a
Move Silently success chance of 100%.  Gary has an Awareness of 120% so his
Awareness success chance to hear Jane sneaking up on him is 120%.
Jane rolls a 43 on her Move Silently.  This is Success Level 2(under half).
Gary rolls a 48 on his awareness.   This is Success Level 2 as well.
Therefore Gary has SL 0 in his perception and does not hear Jane.

Example 2: Alden the Active is swinging his Bastard Sword at Chuck the
Cheeky.  Chuck(assuming appropriate initiative and perception) decides to
parry with his open hand.  Alden's swing chance is 210%.  Chuck's parry
chance(with parry and non-weapon mods) is 160%.  Alden rolls a 98, giving
him SL 2.  Chuck rolls a 12, giving him SL 4.  Alden's adjusted SL is now
negative two: (2-4=-2).  Thus he has two levels of failure on his sword
swing, and probably has to roll to hold on to his sword.

Example 3: Alden the Active gets really mad and decides to Great Blow Chuck
the Cheeky.  He swings.  Chuck opts to do an active defense.  He rolls his
active defense.  Alden gets an amazing 4 SLs on his swing.  Chuck gets 3 SLs
on his DEfense skill.  Thus Alden's adjusted SL for his Great Blow is 1.  So
Chuck gets hit by a SL 1 sword blow from Alden.

Example 4: Alden the Active gets even madder and decides to take Chuck the
Cheeky's head off.  He swings.  His chance is 210% but Chuck's defense is
90.  Alden FSC drops to 120%.  He rolls a 42.  This is success level 2.
Chuck opts to do an active defense.  He has 160% chance.  He rolls a 39 on
his active defense.   Chuck gets 3 SLs on his Defense skill.  Thus Alden's
adjusted SL for his attack is negative one, or SL-1.  So Alden misses
despite his good roll!

PROS:
-It levels the playing field a little.  Lucky low-level people have more
chance of success against high-level people.
-You can use the SL difference to determine things like how much information
the guard got about the person sneaking up on them, etc. how well did she
win the arm wrestling, how critical was the parry....
-it is much faster- all you need to know is what success level you are in
not the exact percentage.  Less addition /subtraction etc.

CONS:
-Slight loss of granularity in the percentages
-It levels the playing field.:-)

