          ON ENDURANCE

In this conversation Physical and Mental Endurances are equivalent.
Therefore we refer to END and EXT- but these refer to both Physical
Endurance(END) and Mental Endurance(MEN).  Likewise for exhaustion.
Physical and Mental endurance and exhaustion are recovered simultaneously
and identically.

Currently END, EXT, and M-EXT (Endurance, Exhaustion, and Meta-Exhaustion)
use the idea that Endurance is like a pool of energy that you have a certain
amount of and that increases as one becomes more skilled.  Actions use up
Endurance like fuel.

***
ENDURANCE:  Basic ""fuel unit"".
It returns after use at 1 per ten counts... usually all back in 3-5 minutes.
Resting or sleeping doubles the return rate.

***
EXHAUSTION: EXT comes off the top of END at a rate of 1 per 10 END expended.
It returns at 1 per two hours of rest, 2 per hour of light sleep, 4 per hour
of medium sleep, and 8 per hour of full deep sleep.  Meals can also restore
1-3 EXT three times a day.  Meditation is as medium sleep.

***
META-EXHAUSTION: M-EXT comes off END as well.  One accumulates one M-EXT for
every 10 EXT one accumulates.
It returns at a rate of: 1 per 4 hours of complete rest(not doing any
activity- not expending more than 20 endurance in an hour), 1 per 2 hours of
deep sleep(Deep sleep is usually achieved in the third hour of sleep)

***
Your first hour of sleep is light sleep and gives you 2 EXT, .25 M-EXT
Your second hour of sleep is medium sleep and gives you 4 EXT,.25 M-EXT
All following hours of sleep are deep sleep and give you 8 EXT,.5 M-EXT

If a character is moving or acting at some percentage of full effort
(travelling with slower companions, taking their time, only punching white
belts) they only expend that percentage of the END cost of the action.  i.e.
if a character has a walk of 1.4 and the group is moving at .7, she only
expends 50% of the END cost for that type of movement.

Levels of critical can be used to decrease endurance cost just like they can
be used to increase damage.  The following table describes the effect:

     Effect of Success Levels on Endurance
1 x2/3
2 x1/2
3 x2/5
4 x1/3
5 x2/7
6 x1/4
...
NOTE: In most cases you need to put at least one success level in a roll to
effect or there will be 0 effect.  :-)  So usually you would never put all
your success levels towards reducing endurance.

***
OPTIONAL RULE:

Whenever the rules call for recovering 1 ENDURANCE, EXHAUSTION, or
META-EXHAUSTION it is read as 1% of the character's endurance.  The amount
of endurance recovered is tallied and then the modifier is applied.
I.e. if a character recovers 54 points over night, and the character evokes
this optional rule, then that is translated to 54% of total and rounded up
to the nearest integer.  This rule will probably only be used by characters
with ENDURANCES over 100... :-)

***
OPTIONAL RULE(DESIGN LEVEL):

PROBABLE: REQUIRES SECONDARY STAT RECONFIGURATION- END AND MEN BASE WOULD
REMAIN THE SAME BUT EXPANSION EFFECTS(LVFs, SKILL EFFECTS) WOULD BE CUT IN
AT LEAST HALF

Endurance costs for skills would be:  COST - RANK*(.05*COST) with the COST
never dropping to zero.
>RNK 1 =  5% reduction
>RNK 2 = 10% reduction
>RNK 3 = 15% reduction
>  (etc.) -           -
RNK 10 = 50% reduction
