PROPOSED TERMINOLOGY - Trash this at will

Mode skills and modifier skills are almost identical in that you roll to
activate them and if you CRIT your levels can amplify the effect, but:

MODE skills enter a mode wherein the effects of the activation continue
until the mode is exited.  These effects often include perceptual bonuses
and penalties as well as the primary bonus effect of the skill.

Examples of mode skills are: Wizardries, Kata and Trances.

MODIFIER skills apply their effects only to the action immediately
following the modifier.  Modifier skills are much faster to activate on
average than MODE skills.  Modifier skills usually have less side-effects
than mode skills.

Examples of modifier skills are: Ki Focus and Florentine

Feint, I think, should be an action like parry.

