"Who sigmund is","Having gone through all of the character chaos surrounding the switch to a new Wizardry model and having generally been pleased with the results of that I thought it would be a good time for Sigmund to step back and see if he could clearly and succinctly state what he is as a character (obviously a grand master of the run on sentance).
 
Here we go...
 
SIGMUND IS A WARRIOR
Sigmund is a MASTER of the longsword (although becuase of his size it looks more like he is wielding a Claymore).  He is also the worlds only MultiWeapon MASTER (having the worlds only MultiWeapon) as well as a mean hand-to-hand fighter.  His style is a generalist fighting style having alot of experience with a wide variety of weapons, including a number of missile weapons, and using his body a lot in combat.  He integrates his fighting very well with Sorcery and DreamWorkings as well as his Fortu abilities.  He has no cultural fighting style but rather displays a mish-mash of curltural styles.  He is a master of small unit tactics and a decent strategic level planner.  He is hard and when dropped from a height tends to leave a crater.

SIGMUND IS A DREAM LORD (Dream Master/Dream Warrior/Herald/Yogi?)
Sigmund manipulates reality at a very internal level.  He is a GRAND MASTER dream walker as well as having a GRAND MASTER level of reality enforcement.  I envision that the same effect which surrounds Lenore also surrounds Sigmund (reality is just much more real in his presence).  At this point he sees and interacts with reality walls as if they were any other terrain feature (slight exageration).  He also has a fundamental control of his own form (shifting Fortu modes, healing himself and altering his size) by internally directed will.  Whether it is player based or character based Sigmund has never spoken as if he had a traditional view of reality.  I envision that at some point Sigmund will be seen calmly walking out of a chaos storm with earth forming just as his foot steps on it and disentigrating moments after he moves on (perhaps I should wait a few more levels before trying that stunt).
 
SIGMUND IS A FORTU
Not exactly the news of the century, but it is a major part of his character.  Sigmund is not human, he reacts differently, he doesn't need to breathe, he can alter his time rate, fractional plane attunement and other things that normal humans might not even realize exist.  As far as Fortu go he is very attune with his abilities and is about to reach MASTER level at being a Fortu with extreme competency in all of the various Fortu SPABS (Also see THE FORTU below).  As far as what a traditional Fortu is, that's a long discussion but lets lop it down into three general areas:  Fortu are fundamentally really tough creatures which can survive in most environments and are really smart and fun to talk to.  Fortu are creatures that have a lot of abilities useful for assisting people (mages, priests, generals, sages,..).  Fortu are creatures that have a lot of abilities useful for killing people (speed, stealth, transverse,...).  In each of these areas, in addition to his Fortu ability skills, Sigmund has reams of relevant more normal skills (Magic Save Skill, Channel Power, G:Stealth for example).  Also, becuase of his ability to shift between Fortu modes (via Dream above), Sigmund every Fortu's Fortu and has skills across the breadth of Fortu experience.

SIGMUND IS A SORCEROR
This is not one of the major apects of Sigmunds character but it certainly is prevalent enough to not ignore.  Sigmund routinely casts sorceries, mostly to support his warrior/assasin roles.  I have not precluded him from casting any sorcery he feels like but in the past he has cast mostly Earth, Matter, Power and Will Sorceries.  He also has some sorceries integrated into some of his Kata making them even more closely related to his warrior aspect.  Sigmund also has some ""Divine Sorceries"" which he uses on occasion but I think I should rework these with Alex since I do not think there is any such thing as divine sorceries.  These are Earth and Souls Divine Sorceries and are used to support his Earth Sorceries and Divine Fortu abilities respectively.  Sigmund is good at all of these but not MASTER level at any and doesn't really ever intend to be.
 
SIGMUND IS A WIZARD OF W:LINES
This is new and still under construction but cleanly encapsulates a lot of Sigmunds prior interactions with magic under one conventient heading.  Sigmund is tuned to the fundamental concepts of lines and dimensions.  He is (almost) a MASTER at manipulating lines of any type.  Targetting lines, DIV lines, lines of directed will etc. as well as things that are expressed along axes such as position.  Based on the current design of this wizardry (Kua-Tao in origin) he can often be seen blinking from place to place around his lab (I remember the bad guy in Golden Child for some reason) as well as demonstrating other odd behaviors (which I will describe in a sperate post).  This is the school through which he does most of his magic.  Unless it is an off the cuff sorcery in combat or a massive Discipline ritual  sigmund is probably using this school (he probably integrates it into all of his disciplines as well - after all never deny a part of yourself when altering reality).  He uses this school a lot for working with Fortu, working with the ward, creating wards and constructs in general, etc.
 
SIGMUND WILL SOMEDAY BE A WIZARD OF W:ALTERATION
This is consistent with his Kua-Toa training and is an open ended plot element but at the moment he has really tiny ranks in Alteration so you won't catch him doing it much.  Besides, I would like to develop some depth around the other skill areas I have first.

SIGMUND IS A DISCIPLANARIAN
Most people in shape shifters are.  What can I say?  I just get this itchy need to stick my fingers into the fine mesh of the very fabric of reality and wiggle them around a little.  Step one, acknowledge the nature of your problem.  Of the discipline related skills I have one third of them are perceptions (in support of the Sigmund is a Dream Lord role), one third of them are Net or Fortu related (in support of the Sigmund is a Programmer role) and the remaining third are the random results of various discipline centric runs.  Mostly Sigmunds style with regard s to disciplines is ritual based except for perceptions and one spell (for lacing wizardries during combat).
 
SIGMUND IS ""THE FORTU""
Not to be megalomaniacal but I consider Sigmund to be the archetypal Fortu both in the sense of his skill set and in his representation as an embodiment of the Fortu racial essence.  As such I imagine that Sigmund has a special rapport with all Fortu that extends to a mystical level (not just that we are on speaking terms).  I also view Sigmund as holding the space for the Fortus ability to do anything and be anything they choose.  I also view Sigmund as the gaurdian of the Fortu race (against being reprogrammed UNWILLINGLY by non-Fortus).  I do not view Sigmund as the protector of all Fortu in a physical sense (if you stick your nose in a big bad battle field you risk getting it singed).  This is an area where Sigmund is currently weak but he is growing rapidly.
 
SIGMUND IS A REALITY PROGRAMMER 
I consider Sigmund to be one of the top ten reality programmers in the world (the megalomania strikes again).  Of course this is only a delusion in my own head.  I speak specifically of that category of reality manipulator which builds discipline based Wards rather than massive will applications or deitic wards.  Do I know what I am talking about?  No.  All right let me try again.  I like Nets.  The net is my home. I like wards.  I like to program the linking ward of Nuryev.  I also like to inhabit other wards (not necessarily the Liche's or the one in the city caves of Salaam - OK maybe like is the wrong word).  If you want to build a ward or a network Sigmund is the person to talk to.  Sigmund is both a MASTER ward programmer and a MASTER net programmer.  At the moment these are the people that I know are better than me: Rhismaeon, Logos and I suspect Ariock and The Liche.  People like Correllan and Dau-Pen are definately better reality manipulators than me but I am not sure if they are better programmers.  I doubt it makes a difference.  Hey, you know what,  the megalomania gets stronger when you approach the areas of the old Nuryev personality.  How intertesting. 
 
SIGMUND IS AN EXPERT ON THEORETICAL REALITY
This may be just another aspect of the above but Sigmund has lore skills coming out of his butt on every subject ranging from theoretical discipline mechanics to elemental physics to theology to planar theory.  He is an avid studier of the mechanics of reality both from the current context and from a wide variety of other viewpoints.  He is also always willing to have a theoretical discussion.
 
SIGMUND IS NURYEV
This is a secret.  Only seven people (in the game) know this so far (Kheldar, Ariock and five Fortu), but it is a plot element and I suspect it will become more of one as time progresses.  BTW:  Nuryev is all of the things that Sigmund is except he is not as much of a Sorceror and he is not a Fortu or ""THE FORTU""  although he is more of a Wizard and much more of a programmer.  He is also a really nice guy.
 

