"Re: Ward of Nuryev and the Heartstone Isolation","First of all, our T-1 is down and so I only got Myths reply so far (as I
suspect is the case for Jim).  Sorry if we have appeared conspicously
silent.

Was there a conspiracy amongst the gods?  I was not aware of any at the time
that I proposed the isolation but I would not be in the least bit suprised.
I never trust anyone or anything.  Was divine influence partially
responsible for the machine getting in such a FUBAR'd state, you bet.  It
was too rapid escalation of the power levels and a series of major divine
reality alterations which was making it likely that the machine would get
blown.  We knew that.  Do the gods hate the machine and would they do
anything in their power to kill it?  You bet, we knew that too.  I would not
trust any of the gods for a second (not even the big A) with the ward.

So what does that mean?  I don't view it as the gods deluded us or conspired
with one of us to pull off the ritual.  To consider that I would have to ask
the question who amongst us was influenced by the gods and the person who
would have had to be influenced was me.  Now it is possible that I was
""altered"" to the point where I felt I had to do it since the only
information Pookie was going on was that Alex said Sigmund recognized that
it was necessary to do.  I think a much more appropriate way to look at it
is that we were forced into a corner.  The gods created a situation (with no
subtelty whatsoever) where the ward and machine were damaging themselves.
They exploited the fact the Rhismaeon is a shit head and destabilizing
things to try and ram himself into the core and take control.  We could have
done nothing and watched the machine destabilize (they win, we lose) or
backed Rhismaeon (they lose, we lose) or do what we did (they win
temporarily, we win in the long run I hope).

I don't know about you but it seemed obvious to me that every dipshit deity
under the sun was going to be creating their own consensus symbol as soon as
the big one went out of scope and I hated this (one mighty ugly way to shake
up the food chain).  I have no idea what is going on that started when we
experienced the Valhalla thing but I did expect that there would be some
major power gambits.

This, by the way, was why I inserted myself into the isolation ward when we
closed it off.  I knew that some mighty major forces were going to oppose us
re-opening the symbol and I wanted to have an edge.  To be honest I was
concerned that Odin might be one of the biggest forces trying to exile the
old symbol.  This is why my top priority of the moment has been the
following:

(Player to Player - Sigmund never tells Kheldar his full plan to kill
Rhismaeon)
1.    Cack Rhismaeon or get him out of the Ward so he will stop killing off
Big Brother.
2.    Reconnect the ward to the Symbol of Consensus and bring it back into
public view.

The only thing which is stopping me from doing all of this NOW is that I am
a little intimidated by the thought of taking on a major discipline mage in
a highly fragile control room right in the middle of Big Brothers brain pan.
I am really worried about symbol growth as well as Rhismaeons progress
moment by moment.

In summary I don't feel like we have been delude or are involved in a
conspiracy.  I feel more like we are in a big chess game and we have just
sacrificed a pawn to avoid checkmate in three.

BTW:  What information do you have on other symbols?  Do you know what is
going on around the bridge?

