"Spell Batteries and different types of spells.","Ahem.  

Brace yourselves.  In my spare time I have been methodically going
through all the assumptions and properties of the spell system.  

Her ecome ssome:  

I originally assumed that ""Incatantion: Summon Air"" and Sorcery: Summon
Air""  Were different skills.    I still operate under this assumption. 

However... what is their relationship?  What if they are the same except
that ""Incantation:Summon Air"" is longer and much more effective but they
do exactly the same thing.  If you vae rank 12 in the incantation can
you do the sorcery at RANK 12 automatically?  

If you have RANk 12 in the working can you add a few spins and a couple
of bows and dust thrown in the air and have a Ritual?  

What if- I am not sure I am proposing this this- rather I am inquiring-
ther eis one skill and it can be done as a:
Sorcery, Wiorking, Ritual, Rite or Incantation.  Maybe we could do it as
familiarity.... If you are familair with it as a working you are -30
with a sorcery or RItual, -60 with a rite and -90 with an incantioation
version.  

It would simplify mages character sheets and would boost a skill's
overal play effectiveness....  WHat do you htink? 

SPELL BATTERIES

Brace yourselves.  I am thinking of getting rid of them.  Now before any
one kills me (likely candidate: Mordanith who has HIGH ranks in SPell
Battery and uses them constantly) I was thinking of transforming the
concept rather than getting RID of it per say.  

I was thnking about WILL and MANNA.  Manna is directed will.  I never
liked storing power points because there are no ""POWER POINTS"" ther eis
only applied will and we measure using a metric called power points.

I was thinking of converting spell batteries into ""Angreal""s like in
Robert Jordan's wheel of time"" series.  They are WILL ENHANCERS.  

Example: 
So if you are a mage- and you have an angreal that Mordanith constructed
it's will-to-ouput ratio might be say, 5:1 (this would be outstanding-
practically an artifact class Angreal) Therefore every point of will you
drew in would give you 5 spell-points for your cast.  So if your 
SCF is 100 and you therefore draw 20 points a count, with that you would
draw 100 points a count.  To use the ANgreal would require a short
sorcery(5 counts, 5 MEN) to activate it.  It would then be ""operational""
for the duration of its use + caster's DRV in counts before it had to be
re-activated.  If you used it before the DRV counts waiting period was
up it would reset to zero so you oculsd use one on-going ly for hours as
long as you had MEN.  They might have a limitation of 1000 points of use
a day or you risk breaking it or something like that(after 800 points of
use ANgreal starts overheating, etc.)  

I like the look-n-feel of this much better than chunks of will strapped
to your belt... what do you all think? 

