"Re: Spell Batteries and different types of spells.","ABOUT INCANTATIONS VS. SORCERY

I must be ahead of my time.  That is the way I thought it always has worked.
I assumed you researched something like Warding ritual (always picking a
default mode) but if you spent longer it would be a Warding Rite (maybe
taking some unfamiliarity mods) and if you wizzed through it it would be a
working (I always assumed that shortening was way harder than lengthening).

I suppose I did draw the line in that I thought Sorceries were completely
different beasts than the Working/Ritual/Rite/Incantation spectrum and I
think this is still true.  After all I can cast a sorcery without a W: but I
can't cast a working.  Also W/R/R/I crowd all require VSMP components
(Verbal/Somatic/Material/Prep) and sorceries do not.  I would argue that it
is good that they are different.  I would not want to see Sorceries becoming
as sophisticated  as Wizardries or Wizardries as fast as Sorceries.

ABOUT SPELL BATTERIES

I think you also have exactly what you are describing in you world.  They
are called Kua-Toa power enhancers.  My take on this has always been that
spell batteries are a specialized conversation of power enhancers which are
made more accessable to human minds by adopting a lot of ""limitations"" which
may not make perfect metaphysical sense.  It is the same issue regarding
time travel or wizardries.  Certain people buy into the limited view of
things because it is part of a cultural paradigm and that makes it safer for
their brains to handle.  Now as for spell batteries I think that part of the
abjurational pattern (pardon me while I design on the fly in somebody else's
sandbox) is the fundamental conversation that mana is a manipulable object.
Of course you and I know that it is not but we also know that physical limbs
are merely a convenient representation for the relative ability we have to
manipulate each other.  It's not true but it is useful for an abjurationist
to pretend that mana is an object.  Once you buy into that it seems only
natural to make a collection device.  Are you actually making an enhancer?
Sure.  You are using a built in macro designed by the people who put
together the abjuration pattern that makes casting this complex will working
easier as long as it has this built in safe gaurd of having use-limiting
characteristics.  Why would somebody build a limited version like that?
Well becuase building Kua-Toa power enhancers is REALLY tough and so this
version is much more accessable to most people.

Now here comes the interesting point.  Why does limiting the spell battery
by introducing the spends and recharges conversation make them easier to
build.  I think the answer is that just making them limited is exactly what
makes them easier to build.  On a discipline level one could ignore the
mechanics of what is going on and just say Kua-Toa power enhancers are
powerful because they are very rare and therefor having one makes you
exceptional.  Spell batteries are less powerful but still very useful
BECUASE they are more common and therefor it is less of a differentiator to
have one.  The level we are talking at here is the level in which everything
is reduced to the fundamental level of who, in a conflict, is more able to
affect the other.  Any items or skills or abilities we have are merely
justifications as to why I am more able to affect you or you are more able
to affect me.  There actual properties are irrelevant except in the way we
by into them.

So back to the issue of spell batteries, I say the reason spell batteries
work the way they do is because some brilliant mage decided that this
limitation fit beautifully with the school of abjuration and served his
purpose.  The purpose that he needed was to find design for a limited
version of the power enhancer pattern because by it's limitation it would be
easier to cast (the universe/mass-consiousness would resist the creation of
these objects less).

Sigmund enjoys having discussions on a theoretical discpline level.

Also, as an element of character I just like the BATTERY design pattern
where you fill it and then it get's used up.  I think the game would be very
different if everyone where running around with always on power enhancers.
Perhaps there are other limitations out there.  A slightly closer to the
Kua-Toa original version that you described was the current limited
amplifier.  Put more than a certain load through it and it blows (possibly
taking you with it).


