Myth triggered off another thought.  One of the things that I have been
playing with in my design of the W:LINES school for Sigmund is that rather
than the skill type you are using, the difference between a rite and a
ritual is the state you are in.  I linked the ritual state (incantation
state,...) to you degree of attunement to the wizardric pattern and also
linked other side-effects to being in that state.  That way the real key to
casting an incantation would be to use your fireball skill while your
character was in the incantation level of tuning to the Pyromancy pattern
and it would just naturally take longer and produce a fire phoenix the size
of a Mack truck with a range of 20 miles. At the same time, by being in the
incantation state for pyromancy you would probably be on fire or be
transformed into elemental fire (maybe in a ritual state you would only have
your hair on fire and a body temperature of 200 degrees celsius).

