"BT Magic: Some elaboration. ","Okay- let me explain something: 

First- what Myth said.

My system does not have a SLIGHT bias that OLD might be better than
NEW.  Old IS better than NEW and a LOT better.  I mean a LOT better.

There are a couple of things which the world is dependant on: 

(a) everyone moves through time at relatively the same pace and in the
same direction.

(b) context generating beings are ABSURDLY difficult to create 

(c) the world as the characters know it- the ""Prime""- has a huge
""reality mass"" and ""reality momentum"" that is based on the millions and
millions of context generating beings who live in that point of view and
the fundamentals of it (elemental structure, some of the rules of magic,
DVF behaviour) are created out of the basic forces that created the
world.  These are- for practical purposes- unmalleable on any kind of
large scale.  At best you could create temporary pockets were those
things were not in place.

(d) all the other places in the ""universe"" (the Abyss, Hell, Faerie, the
Outer Planes, the Bridge) are merely mirrors and shadows of the prime. 
They have almost no reality mass compared to the prime.   This is why
the Prime- and its inhabitants are so critical and why everyone is
fighting over it.  It is also why it was such a big deal at the end of
the Second Chaos War when the BiFrost was set to ward it and lock in the
""rules of engagement"" for the Gods.  

(e) Most of the currently known Wizardries are based on Mardr'a
teachings in the 5 th century after the Second Chaos War.  Legend has it
that a mysterious teacher from before the Ward taught her the Rune Sets
and the basic WIzardries which became the Dorian standards.

There are some exceptions coming from the Naakor, from Rhelania and from
Tharuden.

(f) The Law of Patterns and the Law of Symbols causes patterns using
magic to grow in power as they are used more and more znd as cultures
interface with those they start to drift towards whatever the consensus
is.  I.e. a mage in Ven trying to learn Illusion will ""accidently""
develop runes and speakings very similar to Ancient Rhelanian and its
rune set. The extant to which it is not related to that is the extant to
which it is ineffective.  This is importnat to get- THERE ARE NO RIGHT
WAYS TO DO WIZARDRY!  the right ones are the one that have been done the
most and whose patterns have the most reality mass behind them.  AS it
grows in power a language might have to be abandoned as a normal
langauge because it is too powerful- the patterns of its speaking can
cause unpredictable results! :-)  

Given that a new, clever language or a new WIzardry is going to be
barely a hyped up sorcery at best!! AT BEST!  The DOrian Wizardries are
EVERYWHERE because they were institutionalized very effectively by
Mardra and sooon everyone began using them and they became the most
popular and therefore the way it is done.  

Older and more used is always better than younger and less used.  This
is not technologhy where the physical prinicples and lawes are out ther
eand we need to design something that uses them better... unless you
discover a ""purwer"" version of a spell that is more effective at tapping
into the pattern than the opne that everyone now uses because of a typo
that happeend in the 10th century in the copy being made of Bob the
Arch-Mages spell book. 

