"Spell Books","Hi,

Not that I have any free time or anything but in the non-free time I do have I have been putting together spell books for Sigmund.  That is to say I have been trying to write down all of the spells Sigmund knows (I feel like the dust has somewhat settled for me as far as Wizardries go) and get statistics for them.

Being the techno dweeber that I am I though the simplest way to do this was to create an Access database and I then created an HTML export (since I hated their HTML built-in HTML reporting).

The results of this can now be seen at my ever growing BT magic web site:
    Goto http://www.foliage.com/~jaw/Wizardries/
    Goto the Drawing Page
    Goto Spell Books at the bottom
    Click on each spell book
I now figured why not capture some of the spells for the more mainstream colleges.  Perhaps this will lead to some uniformity and predictability in spell design.

As such I invite all of you to send me any spells that you have reasonably categorized.

At a minimum for each spell I would need the following:
Name
Wizardry
Type (working, ritual...)
A short description

Additionally if you want to provide it I have room for the following in the database
Cost
DM
Casting Time & Casting Time Units
Area & Area Units
Range & Range Units
Duration & Duration Units
Who Researched it (I will default to you)

If you like I can mail you my Access 97 project complete with tables, a form for entering spells and a printable report for spell books but frankly I would rather centralize it.  Unfortunately I do not know how to put it on-line.  Our HTTP server is Apache and I have never made an ASP page anyway (although the form has an option for saving it as one).  Anyway, I will think of that sometime later when I have more real free time.

BTW:  For other techno dweebs I can rig an XML export very easily if there is interest

