Old races almost entirely wiped out; Lizardmen and Dragons crippled and
enfeebled go into recuperation; Dau-Penn and Kisereth banished...little
animals spread, breed and form.  ""Balance "" established? 

Year 500  
First Dwarves, Ogres, Wolves

Year 2500
First Humans, Gnomes, Giants

Year 4000
First Dwarven city built.

Year 7,500
First human ""towns"" in Ven

Year 9,000
First Tharuden city formed.

Year 9,100
Second Tharuden city built.  First High Elven city built.  

Year 9,400
First wood elves.

Year 10,000
God-King and Rhanouin Shadow-Walker born

Year 10,100
Human tribes inhabit what will be South Hetasia and Kereshay Desert

Year 10,500 
First High Elf ""Emperor"" forms capitol of new ""nation"" on site of
ancient Epoch 3 ruins and builds an army to defeat the Lizard men of the
Gallic Sea.

Year 10,600 
God-King becomes King of one of the three city states that sit on the
peninsula of Tharuden.  First written record of the mage known as
""Nureyev"" in Tharuden as an ""advisor"" to the God-King.

Year 11,000
Mephistopheles is born.  

Year 11,100
Chiang-To, the second High Elven ""emperor"" declares the three
city-states of the high elves as the ""World Empire"".  Begins enslaving
humans and Lizard men.  Begins using artifacts and magics not seen
before in this Epoch.
Cuts off ties with originating Elven church and avatars (now known as
""Gray Elves"" because of the color differential - the high elves on the
prime were a golden yellow in color).  Corellan was notably silent on
the matter to the surprise of the Elven Church- so it was allowed to
happen.

Year 12,000
The Empire known by the humans as the ""Golden Empire"" expands to cover
more territory starting to absorb fledgling human ""states"" and killing
or enslaving all the populations therein.

Year 13,000
GodKing declared as a God by his people- against his will 

Year 13,350
Early Fortu models built/appeared/etc.

Year 13,500
Machine ummmm ""appears"" ummm no is ummm ""built""  Ummm...

Year 13,790
Linking Ward ummmm ""appears"" ummm no is ummm ""built""  Ummm.

Year 13,900
Classical Fortu ummm.. ""invented"" ummm ""appear"" umm.. :-) 

Year ~16,000
The Five make their deal with the Gods re: the Machine

Years 14,000 - 18,000
Stuff happens.  Lots  of stuff.  The Golden Empire grows alot- covers
more of the prime.  The Golden Emperor has more power than the Highest
Priest of Corellan in Faerie.   The Quentar declare the ""Golden Elves""
anathema and break all contact. Corellan and Avatars are still ""no
comment"" on the matter. The Golden Emperor encourages non-corellan
worship of Dark and Strange Gods.  
A council of Wizards begins to have the real power in the Empire. 
God-King successfully fights off Empire again and again.  Nakor
develop.  Judges form.

Years 18,000
Lizard Men are almost wiped out. Great magics are born/re-discovered.   
Somewhere in here in a remote human hunter-gatherer tribe a woman was
born- she would be captured, become the slave or a great Golden One
wizard and, eventually, kill him and steal of all of his magics. She
would become an Eldar.  

Year 19,000
The great mage Grumsh invents Orcs.  Mephistopheles becomes the advisor
to the Golden Emperor.

Year 19,800
In the human city of Kestor a human named Arken is born.   He becomes a
paladin of Asmonar, a Herald, and a great general 

Year 20,300
Trouble in paradise. Some mages breaking off from Golden Emperor.  
Humans to the North are gathering together and organizing with
Elven(Quentar) help.  Human cities of Taroll(Quentar help) and
Kestor(help from Asmonar) and Koreth(help from God-King) all fighting
off the Empire.  Internal disputes starting to interfere with the Golden
Empire war machine, corruption and greed has taken its toll.. The once
great armies are poorly organized and involved in a giant civil war
(which is why the human cities are ""winning""- it is much like the
American revolution).

Year 20,378
Usul is born in the city of Koreth.

Year 20,400
In the city of Taroll two twins are born to the Chief of Taroll's wife: 
Heimdell and Aeroch.  Prince Taliesen and Marius Two-Blade of the
Quentar take on the training and development of those two.

Year 20,403
Usul becomes the youngest arch-mage in human history at the age of 25. 

Year 20,410
Arken becomes the King of Kestor and takes Marius Two-Blades and Aeroch
into his court and sends his son Davin to King Mallus' court.  King
Mallus sends his other son Heimdell to Koreth.  The three kingdoms form
an alliance (cemented by the trading of sons) called the Tri-Partite
Alliance.  It fights against the Golden EMpire.  Doesn't do much except
to keep its cities from being destroyed.

Year 20,418
Aeroch becomes a paladin of Asmonar, and Marius and he fight - a fight
in which, rumor has it, he kills Marius.  He is said to be the most
gifted blade master in the world at the age of 18.  Marius disappears.

Year 20,420
Heimdell becomes a paladin of Dof-Sifrin at age 20.  He and Taliesin
return to Taroll.
Usul's temples- which he calls ""libraries""- are in every human city and
settlement in the world.  Usul refuses to become a God and becomes an
Eldar at the young age of 43.  He preaches the dangers of force and the
importance of education.  Rumor has it that he has mastered ten schools
of Wizardry.  Assassins constantly try to kill the Preacher but he
always survives.

Year 20,500
Heimdell becomes the leader of his people after his ""father"" Mallus
dies.  Aeroch becomes a Herald- a lone swordsman wandering the earth. 
Heimdell begins training under Usul, Taliesin, and other Great Mages in
the arts of Magic.  
The Tri-Partite Alliance still barely holds on against the corrupt and
divided  Golden Empire. 

Year 20,600
The Archmage Gruumsh invents Trolls.  He unleashes them on some of his
political enemies.  They die.  He prepares spells and tokens to control
them so he can use them against the Tri-Partite Alliance.

Year 20,630
The Golden Emperor gathers an army together based on Gruumsh's promise
that the Trolls will be ready.  He sends his army forth against Kestor.  

Year 20,631
Kestor falls.  The devastation is horrible.  Most of the population is
killed and sacrificed.  Huge rents in reality are torn through the
Prime.  Trolls are unleashed and released into the city.
Arken and few bands of survivors flee and re-gather- then sue for
peace.  

Year 20,632
Asmonar uses the destruction of Kestor to launch an attack of Death
against all of humanity. Aeroch rebels and revokes his oath to Asmonar
and then flees Asmonar's wrath.  

Year 20,633
As the armies of the Golden Empire crush Koreth humanity flees and
gathers itself to Taroll the weakest and smallest of the human nations. 
Tharuden holds its borders and remains neutral (though constantly
bleeding weapons and high magic to the humans).  The God-King,
Dof-Sifrin, Corellan's advisors, Heimdell and Usul's people are
constantly feverishly working on a desperate plan to stop the Golden
Empire and Asmonar's plague that he has unleashed (it is guided by four
incarnates Asmonar invented:  Death, Famine, Plague, and War).

Year 20,634
Heimdell masters the Eighth School of Wizardry and the Third Discipline
under the God-King, Usul and Dof-Sifrin's tutelage.  They prepare a
Discipline Two invokation of Tremendous Power.  Their code word for the
top-secret project: ""BIFROST""  Arken, now the Incarnate of Death, 
continues to lead his rebel armies against the Golden Empire while
cutting a swath of death through the humanity he once belonged to.  

Year 20,635
The LAST YEAR of this era.  (epochs::eras::centuries::years:months)  The
beginning and the END of the Second Chaos War.  

Month 1
Usul destroys himself and the Orb of Light on top of Olympus Mountain
after having summoned Asmonar there.  Asmonar is Discipline Two
