Ummm... I don't have time right now....

> Who exactly was asmonar?

Asmonar was a Greater God on the level of King Correllan, Dof-Sifrin, Dau-Pen,
Kisereth.
He ruled Death and was strongly allied with Darkness.  He was violently opposed
to Humanity but more opposed to the Golden Empire.

> God-King        ???

The God-King of Tharuden.  He is an immortal Eldar.  He has ruled the peninsula
of Tharuden (think lush tropical river valley sort of environment) for thousands
and thousands of years.  He is the ABSOLUTE ruler of his people and they do not
expand nor do they ever contract- they are.

> Rhanouin Shadow-Walker  ??

An Eldar.  Nothing more to be said about him...

> Mephistopheles - Golden empire?  Human

He is one of the Golden Ones that made up the Golden Empire (half-Quentar,
half-Human that replaced their alliance to Air with an Alliance to Earth and
Fire, and chose the elven path at a young age).  He survived the fall of the
Golden EMpire and it is said he sold his soul to Kisereth and replaced his Light
with Darkness.   He founded the ""Black Cloud"" society of assassin/mages.  Rumor
has it that he is recently (1 year ago?) deceased at Kay's hand.

> Nakor   - Same as golden empire?

The original Na-Kor were either Golden-One human cross-breeds or Golden One
children that choose their human heritage instead of their elven.  They have
since inbred and become slightly different than that.  They are very rare, but
very powerful sorceror/warriors.

> Judges ??

The Judges are a Dal-Kon order of monks.  They are trained in a ""Tae-Kwon-DO""
like martial art and in intense ""KI"" skills, they are also trained to Truth-Read
and perform other sorcerous functions.  They are well versed in the Law and in
Dal-Kon they can arbitrate any dispute and their decisions are binding- even on
Samurai and Daimyo.  However another Judge can dispute a ruling, and the current
Emperor is flexing his muscle in terms of being able to veto a Judges decision.
Briand Beaudin's character Wei-Li is a Dal-Kon Judge.

> Grumsh - Golden Empire

Grumsh was a Golden One wizard/biologist.

> Arken - Starts good, goes bad?

Arken was a human who became a Paladin of the Greater God of Death.  He was also
a Prince of Kestor.  When he became King he was tremendously successful at
repelling the Golden Empire (until they unleashed Gruumsh's Trolls and the
Preceptors on his city).
Asmonar gave him the Incarnatehood of Death.  He is the only one who survived
the fight against Aeroch  on what would be Fire Mountain.  He then fled and
after recovering he took Asmonar's throne in the reality called Hell and has
been the God of Death since then.
The Lich ""TECHNICALLY"" serves Arken.

> Asmonar - Helps found human cities - then cause plague?

God of Death- see above.  He was looking for worshippers- then sucks their souls
when they die.  When the Golden EMpire overran Kestor he figured he better cash
in one as many human deaths as possible since he figured the model was going out
of style.

He was surprised when he was killed by one! :-)

> Usul

WHat is there to say?  You have his life story- a human, unbelievably talented,
is still worshipped today in cities all over the world.  Considered a ""God"" of
learning, light , and charity.

> Aeroch

Arioch.  Knight of Swords.  Immortal being that was human.  In this linear
chronology was Heimdell's twin brother.

> Hiemdall

Yep.  See above.  When he cast the Bi-Frost Ritual he bound himself as the
watchdog and the guardian of the Ward around the world.  He hasn't left the
Throne of Power on the Bi-Frost since then.

> -Britt

Human engineer and role-player.  Bound to another human, Rita.  His current
impact on the world is still being worked out by history....

