"Re: BT: Years and Months and Days","Hmmm..... it is not precise.  Days and seasons are longer and shorter
based on the current state of balance between light and dark (i.e. who
is winning!:-))  However there are some generic things...

I, after some fooling around, standardized on a calendar like ours
because it drove players crazy otherwise.  Thus:

There are 7 days in the standard week.  The Messenger (the smallest and
fastest moon goes through its cycle in approximately this time.)

28 days in a month- for the sake of my sanity the Dragon (the biggest
moon) follows this schedule like clockwork.  The 28th is always the last
day of the full moon.

There are 12 months in a standard cycle of seasons.   Therefore there
are 336 days in a year.

There are 24 hours (more or less) in a day.   There are 60 minutes in an
hour and 60 seconds in a minute.  However- except for ritual Wizards
people don' t use seconds.  They use:

candlemark -> 15 minutes
heartbeat -> ~1 second
the quarters of the day-> noon, midnight, dawn, dusk-> also
mid-morn(9:00am), mid-work(3:00pm), mid-rest(9:00pm),
mid-sleep(3:00am).  In Maera they use the prayer station names for
these.

    -> The Tolnians began using hours about five hundred years ago as
they developed more accurate time pieces.  (They still need to be reset
at noon every day but....:-) )  Hours caught on in Doria and Dau-Sho but
no where else.  They caught on in Maera and the Franksih Lands as well
but they were called ""bells"" because the Churches tolled the hours.

