"Theories about magic","Alex and I were talking about Alteration in the parking lot and trying to determine if my (Kua-Toa) school of alteration differed from the common (Slaad based) school.  I had not thought about this before becuase I did not realize they were different patterns.  This prompted me to expound Jim's theory of how I though of the magics (from the Kua-Toa vs. Slaad perspective) so that Alex can then explain what the case actually is.  So here goes:

1.    Jim's History of Human Magics

Life in the Third Epoch
  a.. Sigmund/Nuryev/... is a Master Drawer.
  b.. Drawing is an Eldar Kua-Toa school created during the 3rd Epoch and was one of the major Kua-Toa wizardries
  c.. Dreaming is an Eldar Slaad school created during the 3rd Epoch and was one of the major Slaad wizardries
  d.. Drawing and Dreaming are violently opposed patterns are war against each other
  e.. Kua-Toa and Slaad are violently opposed races and war against each other
  f.. Members of the Kua-Toa race also studied eldar versions of the Alteration and Summoning schools
  g.. Members of the Slaad race also studied eldar versions of the Alteration and Summoning schools
  h.. My impression was that Kua-Toa Alteration and Slaad Alteration were two (very different) schools of the same pattern
  i.. Similarly with Kua-Toa and Slaad Summoning
  j.. A non-Kua-Toa who learned Drawing would react violently to a non-Slaad who learned Dreaming
  k.. A non-Kua-Toa who learned Kua-Toa Alteration would not react violently to a non-Slaad who learned Dreaming becuase these patterns are not fundamentally opposed (except maybe a culturally aqcuired antipathy)
  l.. Anyone from the current epoch who tried to learn drawing or dreaming would most likely destroy their brain

Life in the Current Epoch
  a.. Conjuration and Evokation are patterns directly constructed by the Kua-Toa based on the drawing pattern which are accessable to the denizens of the fifth epoch.
  b..  Illusion and Enchantment are patterns directly constructed by the Slaad based on the dreaming pattern which are accessable to the denizens of the fifth epoch.
  c.. Abjuration, Divination and Will Working are modern patterns that are based upon both drawing and dreaming.  They were created as seperate efforts with the God-King patterns being more drawing based (I wonder why) and the Golden Ones patterns being more dreaming based.  Over time these schools have merged to form a single pattern although some flavor still remains (prophecy is more dreaming, seeing is more drawing).
  d.. Alteration and Summoning(Greater) are modern versions of the eldar patterns which have been generally made accessable.
  e.. I have not though about the elemental schools at all.  I do not know if they are Kua-Toa, Slaad or none of the above. If I had to guess I would say that they are not Kua-Toa but are made possible by the Kua-Toa patterns, except for life and death which are heavily Slaad influenced and nature and decay which are a big blend.
  f.. Madra came along late in the game and mixed all of the patterns together a little and tended to muddy the waters about their roots.  I am unclear how she and Asmonar relate to each other and the elementals but that is less relevant to this discussion.
Anyway, the whole reason for this was that I see the Alteration and Summoning patterns as being developed and practiced by the Kua-Toa and Slaad but less racially aligned than Drawing and Dreaming.  I see all the Higher Wizardries (other than Alteration and Summoning) as having been derived from either Drawing, Dreaming or Both.  And I don't know about the Elemental Wizardries.

2.    Jim's View on Alteration

We were also talking about how alteration works.  In retrospect I think we were saying a lot of the same things in different ways therefor I think I would list a few of the key aspects of alteration and then we can invent flowery language to express it in the game (my favorite part).
  a.. AN ALTERATIONIST ALTERS THINGS TO A PATTERN - An alterationist does not have to know how something works or what it is made of two shift into it or alter something into it.  The first step in an alteration is to call the pattern of the thing you are altering into.  You do not issue each micro alteration instruction with the risk of screwing up and turning into a dog with a non-functional heart.
  b.. AN ALTERATIONIST ALTERS SUBSTANCE AND FORM BUT NOT WILL.  If I alter myself into a pig I will develop the senses and maybe some of the personality of a pig but I will still BE sigmund (be the same CGB) and I will have my intentions and ""memories"" (this is probably a complex area but hopefully we can just go with it for the common case).  I cannot alter someone to be sad.
  c.. AN ALTERATIONIST ALTERS THE PROPERTIES OF AN OBJECT  - If I alter a lump of gold into a wooden pail and then someone does a detect gold on the area the pail will not show up as gold (or there would be a contest of skills but the default would be to have the label of the new thing).
  d.. AN ALTERATIONIST DOES NOT ALTER THE IDENTITY OF AN OBJECT - If I alter gold into a wooden pail and then wild magic comes into the area there is a chance that the pail will pop back into the lump of gold.  This is becuase the pail is fundamentally a lump of gold in pail form.  It would take, however, a discipline level divination to detect the true identitiness in this respect (or a really cranking roll in the contest of skills for a wizardry based divination).
  e.. AN ALTERATIONIST ALTERS RELATIONSHIPS - From the Kua-Toa perspective an alterationist is altering the consensus relationship properties of a CGB with respect to other CGBs and the ""world"".  As such the things which are altered sometimes transcend the physical.  If a high level alterationist alters into a dwarf they could, as part of the change, alter their native tongue to dwarvish.  If a high level alterationist turns into a fish they could transfer their familiarity with ground based movement to a corresponding skill with water based movement.  (Actually, this may be the difference between Alteration and Ki Factor Shapechange in which case I should rewrite the Alteration advantages a little).
  f.. AN ALTERATION IS ""PERMANENT"" - Once an alteration is made, in the absence of any other magic (as in case 4 above) the thing will stay altered and over time the new pattern will become more and more of the base pattern of the entity till eventually it becomes both permanent and not an alteration.
Beyond this I had a lot of words about fundamental patterns which I think are applicable as long as we agree on the operational definitions.

3.    Jim's History of the World

As long as I am pontificating I thought I would divulge my secret interpretation of the history of the world.  I believe each epoch in history is defined by a fundamental conflict.  This conflict represents, at one level, the stage in the evolution of the universal conciousness.  This conflict also represents the fundamental cause of the major battle which defines the end of the epoch.  One of the things I see about the fundamental conflicts is that even though there was a battle and a presumed winner each of these wars still goes on.  Also, although one side seems to dominate in each case I do not ever see a 100% victory.  As I see it the fundamental conflicts for each epoch are as follows:

Epoch I - Existence vs. Non-Existence
Epoch II - Group vs. Individual
Epoch III - Objective vs. Subjective
Epoch IV - Order vs. Chaos
Epoch V - ?Life vs. Death?

In more detail:

Epoch I - Existence vs. Non-Existence
  The being awakes.  There is I. Should conciousness maintain itself or should it disappear only to reappear the next moment unaware that it has ever been before.  Such a state could go on forever or it could end and identity could be established.  The sides are basically those who support there being something and those who believe there should be nothing.
  As I see it the somethings won and what came out of this conflict is the concept of context generating beingness.
  This is the age of the elements.
Epoch II - Group vs. Individual

  Now awake the question is am I one entity or am I multiple entities each with a unique viewpoint.  The battle of the hive mind over the individual mind.  I see the concept of divinity coming forward as a distinction in this epoch (am I acting as the whole or as a part).

  As I see it the individuals won (although the divine uber-entities still exist)
  This is the age of the insect.  This is also the age of Sorceries.

Epoch III - Objective vs. Subjective

  Now a series of individuals the question is ""is there anything besides us?""  I see the Kua-Toa supporting a universe in which we live in an external objective framework.  I see the Slaad supporting a universe in which there is nothing real but ourselves and consensus between us is transitory and ephemeral at best.  I see the objective crowd supporting a material world with causal order and persistence.  I see the subjective crowd supporting a dream world in which all things external to us are just expressions ourselves at the current moment and there is no persistence of anything but self.

  As I see it the objectivists won (although we do still dream)

  This is the age of the Slaad and Kua-Toa. This is also the age of Wizardries.

Epoch IV - Order vs. Chaos

At this point I start becoming less in tune with the progress along the path of conciousness.  Having settled on a host of individuals in a persitant and causal universe I see the conflict becoming abstract.  It seems like the fourth Epoch resolves around the Dau-Penn/Kisreth.  This division is most commonly referred to as order vs. chaos but I do not see this as a stage in evolution.  It is more a moral dilemna.  Perhaps the question is more difficult to pin down like Morals or no Morals.  I tend to think it is more metaphysical than ethical.  I will think about this more.

Perhaps I Dau-Penn and Kisreth hate each other but were both on the same team.  After all it would be hard to say one won over the other.

Epoch V - ?Life vs. Death?

As far as the current epoch this is even harder.  It seems that the biggest conflicts here revolve around life vs. death but this could be a thin mask over the whole prime vs. non-prime battle.

Anyway, perhaps I delve to deep.  Time to return to work. 


