"Elven Magic","New strategy.  Rather than think about how elvish magic would work let me state what I would desire out of Sigmund's elvish magic skills.

1.    My elvish magics ought to be completely different in character from my other magics.  Currently Sigmund has one Magic area in three of the four types of magic.  

For Kua-Toa magic he has a Drawing wizardry with the corresponding Kua-Toa discipline skills.  For Draconic magic he is a priest/avatar of the Fortu racial archetype.  For Slaad magic he is a dreamwalker and has various skills in calling from and manipulating the dream.  Each of these skills are so completely different from the others that there really is no comparison.  Trying to use a single word like magic to cover all three would really be a stretch.  

I am sure there are examples of each of these kinds of magic that are much closer to each other.  For example the Tharuden Royal College of Will Working (Kua-Toa) and the Rhellenian Will Working School (Slaad) are very similar and I am sure there is some draconicly influenced 'Wizardry like' thing which is very similar.  The point is that whether or not these things exist Sigmund does not have these kinds of skills.  Sigmund tends to learn things at their core.  One might say that the colleges mentioned above are all human schools and hence are closer becuase the human outlook has blended them and none of them are pure.  It is my contention (completely unsupported by anything so crass as facts or consensus opinions) that in their pure forms each of these three types of magic have nothing in common at all and that there pure forms are never seen in the world today.  Sigmund tries to study each of these magics as close to the pure form as possible.

