"Random Gaming Blurb","One of the things that happened this weekend was I had a short discussion with Alex about the fact that there is no foolproof way to teleport.  The safest plan Alex could come up with was:  when you get to be rank 16 in teleport like Falstaff and are as deadly maybe then you can teleport with impunity, maybe.

Rather than get all bummed out and never go anywhere again I figured why not look on the bright side and explore what the advantages and disadvantages of my other form of fast transport (shifting through the net) are.

What is the net (in sigmunds opinion)
The net is a tightly woven web/fabric of tendrils which permeates all of reality (realities).  It is composed (much as the internet is) of a bunch of disparate subnets which have been glued together.  Many of the networks in the world are probably aspects of the net seen through specific world views and many of the parts of the net has acquired the flavor of its most frequent users.  Some subparts of the net which I have travelled across include the Halls of the Dead, the Golden Empire Network, the Tarrantyl (sp?) Pattern and the Liche's Network.

How do I travel through the net (in sigmunds opinion)
I cast a spell to move to a reality in which the lines of the net are a physical place and then I walk along them until I come to a part of the net near the reality I want to be at.  Then I cast another spell to move back to the reality I wanted to be at.  While I am in the net I can look out (using a special variant of the 'See Planes' sorcery) at the reality supported by the part of the net I am in.

What is it like to travel through the net
For me I see the net in one of two modes:  

In physical mode I see the net as large tunnels with  milky gray walls of an unknown substance.  The tunnels are about the size of a subway tunnel and can junction off in any direction including up or down.  Any entity can use whatever form of locamotion is natural to them (so Kilsorana can swim next to me walking).  It is VERY VERY tangled and easy to get lost in which is VERY deadly since some passages mysteriously empty into the void with no warning.  While in the net there is no access to any of the wizardric patterns or any divine entity unless that pattern/entity is manifested inside of you (which apparently starts at Rank 10 and the amount you can do when isolated grows slowly with each rank after that).  Areas that are tainted or are part of a subnet may have a different character.  The halls of the dead appear to me to be very blocky square stone tunnels.

In data mode I am a little data packet zipping along a packet switched network with a bunch of other little data packets.  Same network, different viewpoint.

What are the Advantages of travelling through the Net
  a.. The net goes everywhere.  In sigmunds opinion the net is fundamental to reality and there can not be a place that is not touched by the net.  I have found two places (Fire Mountain and The Sea Elven City) which did have networks but the networks were isolated from everywhere else's net.
  b.. I cannot be teleportal trapped stepping into or out of the net.
  c.. When I get to where I want to go, just before stepping out I can look at what is there in case it is ten trolls with jack hammers.
  d.. My buddy Big Brother is there.
What are the Disadvantages of travelling through the Net
  a.. It is not instantaneous.  I travel through the net at an effective rate of 100 times what it would take me to walk there.  In actually I am travelling much faster but there are no direct paths in the net so likely I will go from Marden to Hiendella via the Abyss, Fairy, Rhellania and the Marianas Trench (or equivalent).  For me this roughly translates to about 1000 mph since I am a fast walker.  But that still means it is an hour plus to get anywhere.  Not that I am complaining, that is much faster than walking.  When we had the golem along this got much slower although I am not aware of anything that would prevent me from bringing a horse (besides the fact that I can't ride).
  b.. It is VERY dangerous if you do not know where you are going since a wrong turn can kill you.
  c.. You get random encounters.  We met a few necromancers, some Terethi, a priest of Loki and a golem on my last jaunt.  Furthermore when you meet people there they are ussually not your average farmer.  I would say that scale is way tilted towards vampire level encounters.
  d.. If you are going near Bengali you will run into Liche tainted parts of the net which are not safe.
  e.. If you travel with me and I get killed it is very hard for anyone else to get out of the net.  There are doors which require no special spells to use but they are few and far between.  You would have to be a rank 10+ conjurer to even think of teleporting out and I don't know what that would do.  I am not sure what it would be like to plane shift or plane step out but I suspect it would be a desparation measure only.
Thats all I can think but after listing all that I can see why I would rather walk than teleport.  I am not sure how shifting through the net compares to walking the pattern (which also seems faster) but apparently there is an issue about where you can walk to.

I also would say that the comparison with dream walking would be that dream walking would be much faster, just as silent if not more so, more dangerous in terms of random encounters along the way and FAR more dangerous in terms of possibly accidently getting lost in an isolated reality and never getting back to the consensus.  Needless to say I do not use dreamwalking for casual transportation.

Actually for casual transportation it is probably safest to take a Ghurka.

