"BT Spells - Some BS from Myth","Here's the deal:

For a fair while, I've had problems with Alex's names for the various
degrees of spell-casting (Workings, Rites, etc).

Updating Eman's sheet, I was inspired with a possible re-naming.

To wit:

Cantrips (barely more than sorceries)
  1 caster, can have components, done in seconds
  ex-- ""Air Lance"", ""Chill Beverage"", ""Dry Clean Outfit""

Spells (more complex, using one or more sorceries)
  Usually 1 caster, often components, done in minutes
  ex-- ""Rebuild to Pattern"", ""Regenerate Limb"", ""Summon Elemental""

Workings (using one or more spells)
  1 or more casters, usually ingredients and diagrams, done in hours
  ex-- ""Bind Air Elemental to Weaving"", ""Find Familiar"", ""Spell Trigger""

Rites (time and power-consuming, more complex)
  Several casters, ingredients and diagrams, takes hours to days
  Timing is often a factor
  ex-- ""Time Hammer"", ""Establish Gate"", ""Summon Vordack""

Rituals (the big guns, very complex and difficult)
  Multiple casters, ingredients and diagrams, hours to days
  Timing is always a factor; may not work at all without right
conditions
  ex-- ""Isolation Ward for Heartstone"", ""Return to Epoch Five""



Does this work for people?  Can someone point out the objectionable
parts I've overlooked?  Comments, questions, even arguments welcomed.

                           -Myth.


