"RE: Let's do the time warp again ...","Whoa!

Serious philosophizing there, and about two levels deeper than I usually
deal with BT Reality.


My understanding is as follows:

As an epoch becomes unstable, either through catastrophe or too many
incremental changes, it is ""closed out"" and a new Reality, more in line
with the current consensus, forms.  Many people are unformed in the
process, unable to let go of the old rules.  Many others die or go
insane in the new world, unable to adjust to the new rules.  Others
adapt, and survive, either by reformatting, or by supreme acts of will
(Gods, Dragons, and the like.)

Travel to previous epochs is not 'possible', because the
epoch-transition point is a massive rules-change, and whatever rules you
are using to power your travel (or divination) don't apply on the other
side.  Travel forward -is- possible, and at one point everyone in the
world does it.   It is not -safe-, however, as you usually have to face
the same hazards as everyone else.


Now, the theories:

We did not 'travel back' to a previous epoch.  We interfered with an
attempt to 'bring forward' a piece of a previous epoch, set up by person
or persons unknown.  (Epoch 3 persons would make the most sense to me,
but between epoch-travel, Line and Dream magics, and Discipline II
stuff, I'll admit I'm over my head.)  We broke the device they were
using, and were 'pulled back' in the resultant confusion.

Getting home is possible (after all, everyone here eventually gets to
the Epoch transition, right?)  I am unsure if simply entering
epoch-transition would take us to Epoch 4 (the new consensus reality) or
Epoch 5 (the consensus reality best fitting us).  Or maybe we wander
around in inter-Reality space, looking for the way home.

                                             -Myth, now feeling
cheerful.




