from
> what is viewed.

> What a few people believe doesn't change what IS.

Agreed.  At least for sufficiently small values of 'few'.  And for
sufficiently physical definitions of 'IS'.

A lot of people used to believe that smoking was cool.  Now, a lot of
people believe that smokers should take it outside, adding pneumonia
to their health risks.  (Note, this is not an endorsement of smoking.
It's a silly and dangerous habit, and trains people to litter.)
Something has changed because of what people believe.

So much for sophistry.

It is possible that what a LOT of people believe changes what IS.
Particularly in the BT universe, where Belief is practically a law of
physics.  I have seen no proof to the contrary in this universe.
(Again, a tricky one to prove..  By the time evidence is found to
contradict the old 'fact', a lot of people believe something else.)



