"Gaming - Death vs. Termination","Just another thought now that I have the old brain running on something
interesting.  So what is this thing called death anyway?  It occurs to me
that death and life are probably recent concepts (epoch 4).  Let me tell you
why.

First of all let me clear up something that bugs me occasionally because I
play a character with no life or death and yet people still want to kill me.

I think there are two fundamental concepts independant of life and death:
Termination and Initiation.

I think that these concepts did not exist prior to the third epoch and are
natural offshoots of the world network.  Non-existance has existed from day
one but I will assert that it is very different for Sigmund to get killed
(non-existance is more life falling into the void).

I think termination and initiation have to do with being connected to a
consensus.  If you have a consensus with any authority you need a way for
the consensus to take an individual and say, ""Nope - your current worldview
breaks the rules - you need to junk it and start a new one"".  Notice how
this does not cause the individual to not exist.  It merely says that its
prior reality is no longer viable and it needs to try something different.
>From the perspective of others you become an inert lump of matter, but from
your perspective you just stop, you lose your body entirely including all
memories and then you get a new body including new memories (or more likely
starting with a clean slate - goo goo).  If you anthropomorphize the context
generating nature of us all then it is a big ""Game Over"" and you need to
start a new game (roll up a new character).

As part of the Kua-Toa machinery that was created for the network, there was
a huge recycler.  This recycler represented a coordinating source for
reality wipe and restarts.  One of the things that was probably found early
on was that if you wiped and restarted a node without giving it a seed
reality it would probably reboot in a state that was in violation with the
consensus and need to get immediately wiped again.  The recycler would give
seed reality hints for new reboots so that individuals who were not to in
tune with the network had an easy way to boot into a valid consensus
reality.  Real power hackers could reboot, ignore the hints, scan the
network on startup and control the rebuild of their new reality to conform
to their liking.

Anyway, one side effect of the recycler was that people learned to hack it
and then they could put in requests for specific forms and places when a
rebooting node became available.  This was used by some to put bound souls
into artifacts by grabbing them as they come off of the presses.  Some
people also say that this is the basis for some of the greater summonings
(the horde of demons out there waiting to come in is just a metaphor to hide
the fact that we are creating evil from ourselves - maybe).

Some people say that the halls of the dead are a symbol for the recycler.

In any case termination is the act of the universe shutting down your old
reality and initiation is the act of the recycler giving you boot up hints
for your new reality (applies to people of all elemental compositions).

Now, based on this what is death and life?  At first glance they may seem
pretty superflous.  In fact they are not.  Death magic really has three
independant focuses.  The first is killing people.  The second is undead.
The third is soul manipulation.  I have a lot harder time describing life
magic because, basically, all I see are healers and they seem pretty limited
from my exposure.  I don't feel like I have met a real life mage (except
maybe Madra).

Anyway, from my experience with life and death, it seems that these concepts
are two different world-views with a defined boundary point of the
termination-initiation transition.  Death does not mean the absence of
motion if you are talking to a zombie or a death lord.  Operationally an
undead creature is just as active as a living one.  Even words like growth
seem to apply equally well to a plague as to a rose bush.

My feeling is that life and death are dim shadows of the unity-diversity
struggle.  The big difference I see between living things and dead things is
that dead things seem to live in a much more hierarchical dominating
structure and living things seem to live in a much more independant chaotic
divergent kind of pattern.  I would say that life and death are two
fundamental worldview flavors that are wrestling for domination of the
world.

Furthermore, I would say that death magics and life magics capitalize on the
network by leveraging the termination points and initiation points of the
recycler respectively.  This has to do with the fact that individuals are at
their most vulnerabe during reboot transition.  A necromancer specializes in
manipulating ""souls"" if it can encounter them at their death point.  He can
color their next universe more towards the death spectrum, he can capture
their soul and bind it to the body as a zombie, he can temporarily leverage
their will as a power source before they are released to the recycler.

Similarly a life mage specializes in manipulating souls if they encounter
them at their initiation point.  A life mage might specialize in growing
specific kinds of beings, or using the will of souls in the birth stage
while they are still formative.

This kind of interpretation does lead to the question, If life and death are
related to the network does that mean they are not as fundamental as other
sorceries.  I would say on an elemental level the elements of life and death
are not as fundamental as the big size (earth, air, fire, water, light,
dark).  On a sorcery level I would say in epoch two all sorceries were just
will battles anyway.  I don;t think sorceries acquired an elemental
character until there was a universe to have elements in (but then it
acquired it retroactively).  As such I think the life & death sorceries may
have lagged behind the other elements (awaiting the completion of the
recycler) but they are not any less fundamental.

So to recap:

Non-existance means your CGBness is gone (real bad - worse than a ""be not"" -
more liked voided).

Termination and Initiation means reboot and start over - initiated by the
consensus when the rules say you lose.

Life and Death are reality colorings - manipulating them means advocating
the conversations for domination vs. independance.
Life and Death Magics leverage the vulnerability of individuals at the
termination and initiation points (soul magic) as well as their respective
conversations and basic flavored sorceries.

Nature and decay are probably analogous but I will leave them for another
day.

